														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2470322">
									

<p>They can be both. The SK-BIO Type is more or less a method of classification. It would be like, if you discovered that there were a whole &quot;species&quot; of SCP-so and so, while the SCP number still designates the original. I imagine the Foundation has things like this. They are anomalies but these are not in containment but encountered at sites that are usually designated as anomalies, if that makes sense.</p>

