			<div class="content" id="post-content-2471053">
									

<p>My personal headcanon of unlisted connections:</p>
<p><a href="/scp-427">SCP-427</a> &amp; <a href="/scp-500">SCP-500</a>: Bottled life, and a tightly bound window to its source. Warning: side affects may occur.</p>
<p><a href="/scp-610">SCP-610</a>: A seething orgy of raw life devoid of order, purpose, and reason, endlessly feeding upon itself until it can devour the world. It is known by many names: The hydra. The Oroborous. Jörmungandr. The Serpent. The Demiurge. The Flesh Which Hates. The Devourer. His Undulating Vastness. <em>Yaldabaoth.</em> Here, after millennia, whispers in the minds of the clever apes have once again allowed it to claw through the fabric of reality&#8230;and the infection is spreading.</p>
<p><a href="/scp-2102">SCP-2102</a>: An experiment once attempted to tap into an endless wellspring of life. It succeeded.</p>
<p><a href="/scp-2610">SCP-2610</a>: Science. Magic. Madness. The oroborous does not care how its rebirth occurs. Only that it does.</p>
<p>On a meta-level, Yaldabaoth is the ultimate parasite or disease- every sarkist is a host and carrier, seeking to spread the infection.</p>

							</div>

								
