<p>Heh, the Sarkites are parasites of Yalda - they drain it, &quot;feast&quot; upon it; incredibly powerful (not to mention large, like, *cosmic* large) but it lacks anything other than animal instinct. The Archons are clever though, and showered Ion with praise - treating him as the chosen one while using him as a tool for their eventual release. Ion was a good man, with good intentions&#8230; the Archons also took advantage of their desperation, as they would have otherwise been crushed by the Daevites.</p>
<p>But things go both ways, the sarkites generally oblivious of the role they are playing - spreading, cultivating the necessary &quot;anchors&quot; to pull Yaldabaoth into our world again. Sarkicism *is* a disease:)</p>

