														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2471598">
									

<p>Yep, I get that bit, but there's more than that though. A lot of this is probably because I'm of the &quot;everything is canon&quot; camp and canon welding makes my brain happy, but I see the sarkist/CotBG conflict as two axes of a larger scale game. The Factory and their investor are playing too- war profiteers mostly, but they've got an endgame of some sort. The Fifthists are wild cards- dodging the archons, while trying to&#8230;something. They might even be the &quot;uninfected&quot; form of proto-Sarkism. There's a bunch of other bit players like <a href="/scp-719">SCP-719</a> and <a href="/scp-435">SCP-435</a>, <a href="/scp-1000">SCP-1000</a>, wherever <a href="/scp-1193">SCP-1193</a> comes from, and the fae are tied up in this somehow as well, I think&#8230; but Pitch Haven is a focused view on a thread towards the center of the web.</p>
<p>Basically, its not a cosmic chess match; it's a cosmic game of <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spoons">spoons</a>&#8230; and its amazing how much stuff can get broken over the last spoon on the table.</p>

							</div>

								
